snippet: Adnan Farhan Abdul Latif, a Yemeni man, was ordered freed in 2010 by a Federal District Court judge but remained in captivity after the ruling was overturned.
abstract: Adnan Farhan Abdul Latif, a Yemeni detainee who died at the American military prison at Guantanamo Bay, Cuba, was ordered freed in 2010 by a Federal District Court judge but remained in captivity after the ruling was overturned by an appeals court.
lead_paragraph: Adnan Farhan Abdul Latif, a Yemeni man, was ordered freed in 2010 by a Federal District Court judge but remained in captivity after the ruling was overturned.
